oc:kn_116a7657 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scoring a CLAUDE.md file" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Score six criteria with weighted points: Commands/Workflows (20), Architecture Clarity (20), Non-Obvious Patterns (15), Conciseness (15), Currency (15), Actionability (15). Each criterion scores 0 to max with intermediate levels." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The weighted rubric ensures comprehensive evaluation covering both content completeness and practical utility" .

oc:kn_585d6252 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When reviewing any CLAUDE.md file" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Red flags: commands that would fail (wrong paths, missing deps), references to deleted files/folders, outdated tech versions, copy-paste from templates without customization, generic advice not specific to the project, TODO items never completed, duplicate info across multiple CLAUDE.md files" ;
    oc:hasRationale "These red flags indicate the CLAUDE.md will mislead the AI agent rather than help it" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a63dcc4f a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating the final quality score" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Commands/Workflows and Architecture Clarity each carry 20 points (highest weight). The remaining four criteria each carry 15 points. Total possible score is 100." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Commands and architecture are the most critical information for an AI agent operating in a codebase" .

oc:kn_b7363fd9 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assessing any CLAUDE.md file" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Read the CLAUDE.md file completely 2. Cross-reference with actual codebase (run documented commands, check if referenced files exist, verify architecture descriptions) 3. Score each criterion 4. Calculate total and assign grade 5. List specific issues found 6. Propose concrete improvements" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Systematic assessment ensures consistent, reproducible quality scoring" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_ba529abf a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing or improving a CLAUDE.md file" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A high-quality CLAUDE.md must be dense and valuable — no filler or obvious info, each line adds value, no redundancy with code comments. Instructions must be executable (commands can be copy-pasted, steps are concrete, paths are real)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Token efficiency matters: every line consumed by the CLAUDE.md is a line the AI agent reads on every interaction, so content must earn its place" .

